gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Clippers 121, Warriors 113
gameRecap.excerpt: The Clippers won their sixth consecutive game and improve to 14-10 on the year as they defeat the Warriors, 121-113. James Harden led the Clippers with a season-high 28 points and 15 assists, along with seven rebounds. Kawhi Leonard added 27 points and eight rebounds as Norman Powell totaled 21 points and five rebounds for Los Angeles. Klay Thompson led the Warriors with a season-high 30 points and 8 3PT FG as Stephen Curry added 17 points, four assists, and four rebounds. The Warriors move to 10-14 on the year.
